g.aria-label:
The goal of the game is to get all of your pawns off the board before the other player.
1. Roll the dice to figure out who goes first. The higher number has the red pawns and goes first. 2. Pieces move in the pattern you see above. 3. Roll the dice. Move your piece forward the number of spaces you rolled. 4. You can only exit on an exact throw.

1. You can’t put two of your own pawns in a square unless it’s a rosette. 2. If you land on a rosette, this is a safe spot. 3. Multiple pawns can occupy the same rosette. 4. If you land on a square occupied by the other player, you get to kick their pawn off the board. 5. When it’s your turn you can move any active pawn or add a new one when you throw. 6. If you can’t move a pawn, you lose your turn.
